data.chText: 部分；数量
data.enText: part/amount

data.chText: 要素；基本部分；典型部分
data.enText: a necessary or typical part of sth

data.chText: 价钱是我们决策时考虑的主要因素。
data.enText: Cost was a key element in our decision.

data.chText: 这个故事是非常典型的肥皂剧题材。
data.enText: The story has all the elements of a soap opera.

data.chText: 与客户的关系是这个工作的重要部分。
data.enText: Customer relations is an important element of the job.

data.chText: 少量；有点；有些
data.enText: a small amount of a quality or feeling

data.chText: 我们得保留一些使人感到意外的东西。
data.enText: We need to preserve the element of surprise.

data.chText: 他的说法似乎有点道理。
data.enText: There appears to be an element of truth in his story.

data.chText: 集团
data.enText: group of people

data.chText: （大团体或社会中的）一组，一群，一伙
data.enText: a group of people who form a part of a larger group or society

data.chText: 党内的温和派 / 激进派
data.enText: moderate/radical elements within the party

data.chText: 学校里难管教的人
data.enText: unruly elements in the school

data.chText: 化学
data.enText: chemistry

data.chText: 元素（如金、氧、碳）
data.enText: a simple chemical substance that consists of atoms of only one type and cannot be split by chemical means into a simpler substance. Gold, oxygen and carbon are all elements .

data.chText: 土；空气；火；水
data.enText: earth/air/fire/water

data.chText: 要素（旧时认为土、空气、火和水是构成一切物质的四大要素）
data.enText: one of the four substances: earth, air, fire and water, which people used to believe everything else was made of

data.chText: 天气
data.enText: weather

data.chText: （尤指恶劣的）天气
data.enText: the weather, especially bad weather

data.chText: 我们要冒着风雨去散步吗？
data.enText: Are we going to brave the elements and go for a walk?

data.chText: 经受风吹雨打
data.enText: to be exposed to the elements

data.chText: 基本原理
data.enText: basic principles

data.chText: （学科的）基本原理，基础，纲要
data.enText: the basic principles of a subject that you have to learn first

data.chText: 他教我看地图的基本方法。
data.enText: He taught me the elements of map-reading.

data.chText: 环境
data.enText: environment

data.chText: （尤指动物的）自然环境，适宜的环境
data.enText: a natural or suitable environment, especially for an animal

data.chText: 水是鱼的天然生活环境。
data.enText: Water is a fish's natural element.

data.chText: 电器元件
data.enText: electrical part

data.chText: 电热元件；电热丝
data.enText: the part of a piece of electrical equipment that gives out heat

data.chText: 这个电壶需要一根新电热丝。
data.enText: The kettle needs a new element.
in your element

data.chText: 如鱼得水；得心应手
data.enText: doing what you are good at and enjoy

data.chText: 她在社交聚会上真是如鱼得水。
data.enText: She's really in her element at parties.
out of your element

data.chText: 处于不适宜的环境；不得其所
data.enText: in a situation that you are not used to and that makes you feel uncomfortable

means: (大团体或社会中的)一组，一群，一伙
（尤指动物的）自然环境，适宜的环境

ex.chText: 他们是该组织中的先进分子。
ex.enText: They are advanced elements in the organization.

ex.chText: 速度是这一体育项目的要素。
ex.enText: Speed is an important element of the athletic event.

synonyms.bx: 尤指一整套系统、计划、作品等中最基本或最重要的成分或特征。

ex.enText: There are many components to the machine.

ex.chText: 该系统由各种部件组成。
ex.enText: This system consists of various components.

synonyms.bx: 指一个整体的组成部分，多用于机器、机械系统等。

ex.chText: 这种护肤霜只含天然成分。
ex.enText: This skin cream contains only natural ingredients.

ex.chText: 面粉和糖是烤面包最重要的原料。
ex.enText: Flour and sugar are the most important ingredients in baking bread.

synonyms.bx: 指混合物的成分，尤指烹饪原料。

data.enText: in your element

data.chText: 如鱼得水；得心应手
data.enText: doing what you are good at and enjoy

data.chText: 她在社交聚会上真是如鱼得水。
data.enText: She's really in her element at parties.

data.chText: 处于不适宜的环境；不得其所
data.enText: in a situation that you are not used to and that makes you feel uncomfortable

tr: an artifact that is one of the individual parts of which a composite entity is made up
especially a part that can be separated from or attached to a system
example: a component or constituent element of a system
jealousy was a component of his character
two constituents of a musical composition are melody and harmony
the grammatical elements of a sentence
a key factor in her success
humor: an effective ingredient of a speech

tr: the most favorable environment for a plant or animal
example: water is the element of fishes

tr: a straight line that generates a cylinder or cone
the situation in which you are happiest and most effective
any of the more than 100 known substances (of which 92 occur naturally) that cannot be separated into simpler substances and that singly or in combination constitute all matter
one of four substances thought in ancient and medieval cosmology to constitute the physical universe
example: the alchemists believed that there were four elements

value.def: The different elements of something are the different parts it contains.

example.ex: The exchange of prisoners of war was one of the key elements of the UN's peace plan.
example.tran: 交换战俘是联合国和平计划的一个重要部分。

value.def: A particular element of a situation, activity, or process is an important quality or feature that it has or needs.

example.ex: Fitness has now become an important element in our lives.
example.tran: 现在健康已经成为我们生活中的一个要素。

value.def: When you talk about elements within a society or organization, you are referring to groups of people who have similar aims, beliefs, or habits.

example.tran: 安保部队中的犯罪分子

value.tran: （社会或组织内部具有相同目标、信仰或习惯的）一群人，一组人，分子

value.def: If something has an element of a particular quality or emotion, it has a certain amount of this quality or emotion.

example.ex: These reports clearly contain elements of propaganda.
example.tran: 这些报告明显带有一些宣传的意味。

value.def: An element is a substance such as gold, oxygen, or carbon that consists of only one type of atom.
The element in an electric fire or water heater is the metal part which changes the electric current into heat.

example.ex: With its unique heating element it makes perfect coffee.
example.tran: 其独特的电热元件使它能够煮出非常美味的咖啡。

value.tran: （电炉、热水器等的）电热元件，电热丝

value.def: You can refer to the weather, especially wind and rain, as the elements .

example.ex: The area where most refugees are waiting is exposed to the elements.
example.tran: 大多数难民等待救济的地方都不能挡风遮雨。

value.def: If you say that someone is in their element, you mean that they are in a situation they enjoy.

example.ex: My stepmother was in her element, organizing everything...
example.tran: 我的继母得心应手地料理着一切。

example.ex: Maybe it's because they're so out of their element that they feel the need to talk.
example.tran: 可能是因为他们感到非常不自在，所以觉得有必要说说话。

value.tran: 自在;适得其所;如鱼得水
